## Read Before Acting

Read these files in order before making any change. They are the minimum context for acting
correctly in this project.

- `core/principles/development-principles.md` — development principles that apply to all projects.
- `core/rules/token-efficiency.md` — token discipline rules; apply them to every model turn.
- `core/rules/maintainability.md` — the six maintainability dimensions; required for every code change.
- `core/rules/model-routing.md` — routing decisions between local and cloud model tiers.
- `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` — compact, durable context for this project specifically.
- `CODEMAP.md` — file and module map; use it to locate code before scanning the repo.
- `VERIFY.md` — verification commands; run these after every change.

## Verification Commands

Verification commands are in `VERIFY.md`. Run the full sequence after every code change
before reporting the task complete.

## AI Policy

Actions permitted and restricted for AI tools working in this project are in `AI_POLICY.md`.
Read it before taking any action that writes files, runs commands, or calls external services.

## Maintainability Constraints

Project-specific maintainability rules that extend the core six dimensions are in
`MAINTAINABILITY_NOTES.md`. The core dimensions in `core/rules/maintainability.md`
still apply; project notes add constraints on top.

## Skills Available

- `core/skills/idea-to-prepared-task/SKILL.md` — captures a vague idea and produces a structured
  task brief queued for execution at a chosen time. The hero skill for v0.1.
